inican nun Margaretha Ebner dating from the second quarter of the 14th century. The study reads the letters as spiritual missives with something of a mystagogical character; this interpretation is then supplemented with a reconstruction of the history of their genesis and transmission and a location of them in their mystical context (Mechthild of Magdeburg, Heinrich Seuse [Suso] et al). The work is an impressive study in cultural history which develops the function of literary communication for religious self-interpretation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aMysticismzGermanyxHistoryyMiddle Ages, 600-1500. 0aMysticismzGermanyxHistory. 0aSpiritual lifexChristianityvEarly works to 1800. 0aSpiritual lifexChristianity. 4aBrief. 4aHeinrich von Nördlingen. 4aMargaretha Ebner. 7aRELIGION / Mysticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2009z9783110219517oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2009z9783110219470oZDB-23-DGA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET MEDIÄVISTIK 2010-2012z97831103011680 cprintz978311020629640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311021696740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110216967423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110216967/original  a978-3-11-030116-8  E-BOOK PAKET MEDIÄVISTIK 2010-2012c2010d2012  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2009  aZDB-23-DGGb2009  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014